CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1956, pg. B1, reads: "'Eleanor Among Friends' - Allegheny County Democrats turned out in full force on Oct. 18, when Mrs. Eleanor Roosevelt delivered a series of speeches in behalf of Stevenson and Kefauver, as well as all Democrats running for Federal and state offices. The picture above shows platform guests in Schenley High School Auditorium, where Mrs. Roosevelt shared speaking honors with Joseph S. Clark, candidate for the U.S. Senate. Reading from left to right are Mr. Clark, Mrs. David L. Lawrence, Mayor Lawrence, Mrs. Molly Yard, Mrs. Roosevelt, Thomas E. Barrett, Miss Genevieve Blatt, Paul F. Jones, master of ceremonies; Joseph M. Barr, Howard B. Stewart and Andrew M. Bradley. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Audience standing before women and men on stage, including: Joseph S. Clark, Alyce Lawrence, Mayor David L. Lawrence, Molly Yard, Eleanor Roosevelt, Thomas E. Barrett, Genevieve Blatt, Paul F. Jones, Joseph M. Barr, Howard B. Stewart, and Andrew M. Bradley, in Schenley High School Auditorium for Adlai Stevenson campaign event
